defaultChair:default Of the charitable sector?  But they represent chief executives. 
defaultMartyn Lewisdefault: Well, because they represent the chief executives within the sector. We represent different parts of the sector.
default&#xa0;
defaultQ24 default&#xa0; 
defaultChair:default You do not see one as a trade body and the other as a trade union.
defaultMartyn Lewisdefault: I certainly see ACEVO as a trade union. I have no doubt about that, because they are looking after the interests of their chief executives. They have recently expanded into one or two other areas, but that is up to them—that is down to their board and the decisions that they take.  
defaultChair:default Thank you for that clarification.
