defaulthe statement of recommended practice,
default which is the accountability framework that sets the parameters over which charities disclose various information around how they raise, spend, invest, etc. their money, 
defaultalready has within it information about the disclosure for charities with a gross income over £500,000 of all salaries—not specific levels of staff—that exceed £60,000, within bands.
